\f1\b\fs48 \cf2 \strokec2 PRD: Contextual Sales Engine (CSE)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf2 Version:
\f0\b0  1.0\

\f1\b Status:
\f0\b0  Planning / Context for AI Generation\

\f1\b Concept:
\f0\b0  Hyper-personalized, AI-assembled sales portals for high-stakes B2B/M&A deals.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf2 \strokec2 1. Problem & Executive Summary\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 The Problem\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Black Box:
\f0\b0  Sales reps lose visibility once a PDF/Deck is sent. They don\'92t know who is reading what.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Burden of Proof:
\f0\b0  B2B "Champions" struggle to sell complex products internally to their stakeholders.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Content Friction:
\f0\b0  Creating bespoke collateral for every lead is manually impossible, leading to "generic fatigue."\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf2 \strokec2 The Solution\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf2 A "Living One-Page Portal" that uses AI to ingest a 
\f1\b Context Pool
\f0\b0  (CRM data + prospect website + internal documents) and automatically assembles a high-conversion microsite. It tracks "Intent Signals" rather than just clicks, telling the rep 
\f2\i exactly
\f0\i0  what the prospect is worried about.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf2 \strokec2 2. User Personas\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The M&A Advisor:
\f0\b0  Needs to show extreme "Proof of Effort" to a target company to win a mandate.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Enterprise AE:
\f0\b0  Needs to provide a "single source of truth" for a multi-stakeholder buying committee (CEO, CTO, Legal).\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The SDR/BDR:
\f0\b0  Needs to break through the noise with a page that says "I did my homework" in under 60 seconds of effort.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf2 \strokec2 3. Functional Requirements\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 3.1 The Context Ingestion Engine (The "Input")\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 CRM Integration:
\f0\b0  Bi-directional sync with HubSpot/Salesforce (Deal stage, company name, contact roles).\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Universal Scraper:
\f0\b0  Ability to index a target company\'92s URL to extract mission statements, recent news, and product language.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Knowledge Base (RAG):
\f0\b0  A private repository for the user\'92s own case studies, security whitepapers, and pricing sheets.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf2 \strokec2 3.2 The AI Orchestrator (The "Assembly")\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Dynamic Component Selection:
\f0\b0  AI must choose 4\'966 "Modular Blocks" based on the prospect's industry and deal stage.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Contextual Copywriting:
\f0\b0  AI generates a personalized "Narrative" (Header + Summary) that connects the prospect's goals to the user's solution.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 One-Page Output:
\f0\b0  The final product is a single, clean, premium-feeling URL (Next.js/Tailwind).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf2 \strokec2 3.3 The Modular Block Library\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Hook:
\f0\b0  AI-written "Why [Your Company] + [Prospect Company] Now."\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Proof:
\f0\b0  Automatically selected case studies from the RAG store.\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Interactive ROI:
\f0\b0  A slider or calculator pre-filled with the prospect's estimated data.\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Implementation Map:
\f0\b0  A visual timeline of the next steps/milestones.\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Shared Drive:
\f0\b0  A secure area for shared documents (NDA, MSA, Technical Specs).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf2 \strokec2 3.4 The Signal Engine (Reverse Analytics)\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Block-Level Tracking:
\f0\b0  Track time-on-component (e.g., "Prospect spent 45s on Security, 5s on Pricing").\
\ls6\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Referrer Identification:
\f0\b0  Detect if the link was opened by a new IP (e.g., "The link has been shared with someone at the HQ in London").\
\ls6\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Intent Scoring:
\f0\b0  A proprietary score (0-100) based on engagement depth and interaction with high-intent blocks (Calculators/Calendly).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \

\f1\b\fs36 \cf2 \strokec2 4. Distinction & "Moat" Strategy\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Zero-Drafting UI:
\f0\b0  Unlike Webflow or Wix, there is no "Canvas." The user provides the URL\cf4 \outl0\strokewidth0 , and the AI return\cf2 \outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 s the page.\
\ls7\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 CRM-to-Live Sync:
\f0\b0  If a deal moves from "Discovery" to "Proposal," the page automatically adds the "Pricing" and "Legal" blocks without manual intervention.\
\ls7\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The "Signal over Data" Dashboard:
\f0\b0  We don't show "Views." We show "Actionable Insights" (e.g., 
\f2\i "Call the CFO now; they just downloaded the ROI spreadsheet"
\f0\i0 ).\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf2 \strokec2 6. Success Metrics (KPIs)\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Time-to-Page (TTP):
\f0\b0  Goal < 60 seconds from CRM trigger to live URL.\
\ls8\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Engagement Lift:
\f0\b0  Do these pages receive >30% more dwell time than a standard PDF deck?\
\ls8\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Deal Velocity:
\f0\b0  Reduction in days spent in the "Proposal" stage.\
